  "texts": [
    "The most successful case is Ψ 2, where our surrogate exhibits a near-zero difference from the ground truth.",
    "In fact, in this configuration, most agents follow deterministic update rules (e.g., dead → dead), which are perfectly recovered by our model, but not by the diffusion-only ablation -which also obtains worse results on stochastic rules, as shown in Supplementary Section C.4.",
    "Instead, the GNN-only ablation performs well only in those deterministic cases, but fails in all the others.",
    "At the macro level as well, the surrogate consistently outperforms the ablation, generally achieving low error.",
    "The best result is obtained with Ψ 1, the most complex dynamics, where the surrogate achieves an average sMAPE of approximately 0.08."
